"{\"uid\": \"news.cgtn.com-news-2024-06-18-Aryna-Sabalenka-Ons-Jabeur-won-t-play-at-2024-Paris-Summer-Olympics-1uwLD4fDT2M-p.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 145, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You can change your cookie settings through your browser.\", \"from\": 146, \"to\": 203, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sports Scene  Copied  Aryna Sabalenka of Belarus competes in the French Open women's singles quarterfinals against Mirra Andreeva at Roland Garros in Paris, France, June 5, 2024.\", \"from\": 205, \"to\": 383, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 355, \"end\": 360, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999973893729901, \"rank\": 2.6106338310150785e-06, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 362, \"end\": 368, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.8526877506815261, \"rank\": 0.1483195533535869, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"/CFP  Two of the world's top women's singles tennis players, Aryna Sabalenka of Belarus and Ons Jabeur of Tunisia, will not participate in the upcoming 2024 Summer Olympics in Paris, the two announced on Monday.\", \"from\": 384, \"to\": 595, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 476, \"end\": 486, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ons_Jabeur\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ons Jabeur\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ons_Jabeur\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ons_Jabeur\"}, {\"begin\": 490, \"end\": 497, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tunisia\", \"score\": 0.9994422047120489, \"rank\": 0.0005370293160049202, \"text\": \"Tunisia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tunisia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tunisia\"}, {\"begin\": 560, \"end\": 565, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999973893729901, \"rank\": 2.6106338310150785e-06, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's too much for the scheduling and I made the decision to take care of my health,\\\" Sabalenka said.\", \"from\": 597, \"to\": 698, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I prefer to have a little rest to make sure, physically and health-wise, I am ready for the hardcourts.\", \"from\": 699, \"to\": 803, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I will have a good preparation before going to the hardcourt season.\", \"from\": 804, \"to\": 872, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I feel that this is safer and better for my body.\\\"\", \"from\": 873, \"to\": 923, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sabalenka is currently third in the Women's Tennis Association (WTA) world rankings.\", \"from\": 925, \"to\": 1009, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 969, \"end\": 975, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tennis\", \"score\": 0.9997960204361019, \"rank\": 0.000204021179825963, \"text\": \"Tennis\", \"types\": [\"Q349\", \"Q1914636\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tennis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tennis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She defended the Australian Open title in January and reached the quarterfinals at the French Open in June.\", \"from\": 1010, \"to\": 1117, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1027, \"end\": 1042, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Open\", \"score\": 0.7332200725665299, \"rank\": 0.363721542152326, \"text\": \"Australian Open\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Open\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Open\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She is currently in Germany preparing for the Wimbledon Championships that will take place in July, right before the Olympics.\", \"from\": 1118, \"to\": 1244, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1138, \"end\": 1145, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\", \"score\": 0.839741756018553, \"rank\": 0.10926150403111617, \"text\": \"Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ons Jabeur of Tunisia competes in the Rothesay Open women's singles match against Karolina Pliskova of the Czech Republic in Nottingham, Britain, June 15, 2025.\", \"from\": 1246, \"to\": 1406, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1246, \"end\": 1256, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ons_Jabeur\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ons Jabeur\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ons_Jabeur\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ons_Jabeur\"}, {\"begin\": 1260, \"end\": 1267, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tunisia\", \"score\": 0.9994422047120489, \"rank\": 0.0005370293160049202, \"text\": \"Tunisia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tunisia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tunisia\"}, {\"begin\": 1328, \"end\": 1345, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karol\\u00edna_Pl\\u00ed\\u0161kov\\u00e1\", \"score\": 0.9999999991221102, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Karolina Pliskova\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karol\\u00edna_Pl\\u00ed\\u0161kov\\u00e1\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karol\\u00edna_Pl\\u00ed\\u0161kov\\u00e1\"}, {\"begin\": 1359, \"end\": 1367, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.87395995368